    "introduction": "An exposition of James 2:14-20 on the relationship between faith and works in the life of a believer, arguing that genuine saving faith is by grace alone but is always evidenced by outward behavior. Old Testament illustrations from Exodus 9 and 16 and supporting passages from Matthew, Luke, John, Romans, Ephesians, Philippians, Titus, and 1 John are drawn in to show that Paul, Jesus, and John teach the same connection between belief and behavior that James addresses.",
